<p class="address">If you are driving, you'll more likely rely on a smartphone or actual paper map than this website for directions, but for good measure;
Groton is about 6 miles northwest of exit 31 from route 495.  From exit 31, follow 119-W, which turns into 225, into the center of Groton, where 225 crosses route 40. The Courtyard is just off exit 31 on route 119.
</p>

  <p class="address">If you are coming from Boston, you'll want to take I-93 N and get off at exit 37. Take I-95 S to exit 32A to get on US-3N. Take exit 30C from US-3N onto I-495 S, then take exit 31 to 119-W.</p>

  <p class="address">From the south or west, take the Mass Pike (I-90) eastbound to exit 10, then take I-290E to I-495N. Take exit 31 from 495. This will bring you to Groton via rt. 119.</p>


